7. .
Issuance of Shares
 
 
(a) Upon satisfaction of all applicable vesting conditions set forth in this Agreement with respect to any portion of such RSU, the Company will settle the applicable portion of such RSU by delivering to the Participant stock certificates, registered in the name of the Participant, or direct the Companys transfer agent to make a book entry, evidencing the shares of Common Stock, with such legends as deemed appropriate by the Company, representing the number of shares of Common Stock underlying the vested portion of the Participants RSU on such vesting date(s), together with any property in respect of such shares held by the custodian pursuant to Section 8 hereof.
 
 
(b) The Company may require as a condition of the delivery of stock certificates, or book entry, as the case may be, pursuant to Section 7(a) hereof that the Participant remit to the Company an amount sufficient in the opinion of the Company to satisfy any federal, state and other governmental tax withholding requirements related to the vesting of the shares represented by such certificate or book entry.
 
 
(c) The Participant shall not be deemed for any purpose to be, or have rights as, a shareholder of the Company by virtue of the RSU grant, except to the extent a stock certificate is issued, or book entry made, as the case may be, therefor pursuant to Section 7(a) hereof, and then only from the date such certificate is issued or book entry made. Upon the issuance of a stock certificate, or book entry, the Participant shall have the rights of a shareholder with respect to the vested Common Stock, including the right to vote the shares.
 
 
