(a) The RSUs granted hereby represent the right to potentially receive Common Stock based upon threshold, target and stretch levels determined by the Committee (with the threshold amount reflecting 25% of TNS and the stretch or maximum amount reflecting 175% of TNS) determined as specified below.  The maximum number of shares of Common Stock that may be earned by the Participant pursuant to this grant agreement over the performance period determined by the Committee and set forth in the Grant Summary is defined herein as .
MNS
 
 
(b) Common Stock may be earned by the Participant based upon the relative total shareholder return of the Companys Common Stock versus the Russell 2000 Index, as described below:
 
 
(i) a straight-line basis ranging from 25% to 175% of the TNS, with 25% of TNS to be earned for at least threshold RTSR (as defined below) of 25 percentile performance and 175% of TNS to be earned for stretch RTSR of 75 percentile (or greater) performance; provided, however, that notwithstanding the foregoing, if the Award would otherwise vest in accordance with the foregoing clause (i) but the annualized return on Common Stock during the applicable performance period is negative, then the Award shall only be earned, in the event of RTSR of 75 percentile (or greater) performance, at 100% of the TNS (subject to negative discretion by the Board of Directors); or
th
th
th
 
(ii) if RTSR is below the 25 percentile but the annualized return on Common Stock during the applicable performance period is above 10%, the Award shall be earned at 25% of the TNS.
th
Promptly following the close of the performance period, the Committee shall determine and certify the level of RTSR performance attained in accordance with the foregoing. Any RSUs that are not earned at the conclusion of the performance period in accordance with either clause (i) or clause (ii) above, based on the level of performance attained and certified, shall thereupon be immediately cancelled.
Upon certification by the Committee of the RTSR actually attained during the performance period, 50% of the Common Stock earned thereby based on the level of performance achieved shall thereupon be vested, provided that the Participant has remained continuously employed throughout the performance period, and such number of shares of Common Stock so determined shall be paid to the Participant in a single sum in all events within 74 days following the end of the performance period.
 
(c) In addition, the remaining 50% of any Common Stock so determined in accordance with subsection (b)(i) and (ii) shall only be vested (except as otherwise provided in Sections 6(b) or 6(e)) provided that the Participant remains continuously employed with the Company through the first anniversary of the close of the applicable performance period; in that case, the number of shares of Common Stock underlying the remaining 50% of the vested performance based RSU, determined in accordance with subsection (b)(i) or (ii), shall be paid to such Participant within 74 days following said anniversary.
 
 
